                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2292</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The French Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chambrun</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to inform
                    Your Excellency in reply to your notes of May 31 and June 5, that the Government
                    of the Republic has approved the resolutions adopted on <pb facs="0558" n="456"
                        xml:id="pg_456"/> May 12 last by the banking groups for the constitution of
                    a new Consortium. There remaining nothing but the nature and scope of the
                    assistance to be extended to the new consortium in China to determine, my
                    Government submitted a draft of formula on that point to the Embassies of the
                    United States and Japan and to the British Government. It is awaiting their
                    replies.</p>
                <p>Be pleased [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles de Chambrun</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
